main event: An unidentified aerial object was visually observed on September 14, 1961, at 10:00 PM local time in the Far East.
interesting points: The object was observed for a brief duration of 0-3 seconds., The report categorized the object as probably a reflection, meteor, aircraft, balloon, or unidentified., The sighting occurred at specific coordinates (36°43'0"N 139°45'0"E)., There was corroboration from the observer's wingman who reported seeing a similar phenomenon., The light from the object illuminated the entire cockpit, leading to the ruling out of the possibility of a falling star.
witness description: Captain Donald C. Windrath, a pilot, and his wingman, usually reliable observers.
